rtance of culturally sensitive approaches in mental health care.\n\nAs the international body responsible for the International Classification of Diseases (ICD) system, WHO plays a crucial role in classifying diseases and health problems globally, including mental disorders. This system provides a standardized framework for diagnosing and understanding health conditions worldwide. Furthermore, WHO provides global statistics on suicide rates and trends, drawing attention to the increasing prevalence of suicide and the urgent need for effective prevention strategies.\n\nThrough its diverse initiatives, WHO continues to address critical health issues, promote mental health awareness, and provide essential resources and frameworks for global health improvement.", "WORLD HEALTH ORGANIZATION (WHO):The World Health Organization introduced a new concept of health in the 1970s, emphasizing physical, mental, and social well-being", "WRAT:WRAT is the Wide Range Achievement Test used to assess learning achievement and language function in children", "WRITERS:Writers are a professional group with a higher suicide rate, potentially due to the emotional and psychological demands of their work."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}